HUGH DONOHO, 200 acs. Augusta Co.
on Divers Lick Br., adj. his own Survey;
10 Jul 1767, p.39. £1.

HENRY ROSE, 400 acs. Albemarle Co.
in the fork of Piney Riv., adj. his Line;
10 Jul 1767, p.41. £2.

JAMES BUCHANAN, 290 acs. Albemarle Co. on Beverdam Cr. of Hardware
Riv., adj. James Hill & Castleton Harper;
10 Sep 1767, p.65. £1.S10.

JOHN JONES, 50 acs. Brunswick Co. on
a road; adj. Sayer, Roberson & Jackson;
10 Sep 1767, p.88. 5 Shill.

FRANCIS THRUSTON, 106 acs.
Goochland Co., down the little Bird Cr.;
20 Jul 1768, p.328. 15 Shill.

OBADIAH WOODSON, 190 acs.
Bedford Co. on both sides of Lick Run;
adj. Perry, Mobberly, Paulson & Phelps;
20 Jul 1768, p.344. £1.

RICHARD JONES, 38% acs. Norfolk
Co. adj. Edward Butt & Willis Wilson;
20 Jul 1768, p.370. [5 Shill.]

HENRY MILLER, 70 acs. Augusta Co.
on dry run near the foot of the mountain;
20 Jul 1768, p.375. 10 Shill.

CHARLES SMITH, 330 acs. Halifax Co.
on both sides of Morris's Cr., adj. Byrd;
20 Sep 1768, p.400. £1.S15.
